And my soul was sold with my cigarettes
To the black market man
I've had the Vietnam cold turkey
From the ocean to the Silver City

Well she was like so many more from that time on

Till they found their chosen one

But their minds were always closed

Title: Waiting
Lyrics:
Invincible LyricsConsider this my soundtrack, this is just a sound byte
From the motion picture that revolves around life
Living in projects, growing up around mice
Not to mention rats, all the boosters down in Crown Heights
Single parent home where you mother ain’t around nights
Working double shifts, barely keeping on house lights
Making sure tuition paid and my words pronounced right
Life doesn’t short change me so I know count twice
No it doesn’t nice, it’s downright atrocious
But she built the character that made me ferocious
Relentless and focused.  Go hard, there is no risk
Turned our hopelessness back into courage
The cowardly lion on the yellow brick road
Has the heart of a lion that the king of jungles
This baby Simba has grown like his father
Now they hear me roar and I resemble Mustafa
Chorus:
Assassinate my character, slander my name
Say what you will but I shall remain
I’m invincible I-I-I’m Invincible  (6x)
I’m sitting on the sidelines , like “what am I waiting for”
Gillie’s telling me it my turn, I gotta take it all
I hear all the rumors, I just brush the haters off
If you don’t believe in me, why you wanna stay involved
Know your role, play your part, you don’t got a hand in this
You are just an agent, I am Mr. Anderson
Knowing what I’ve overcome, I feel like a champion
All I need is room to hang my championship banners in
Came from the bottom and rose to the top
Playing the possum and honing my plot
Sticks and stones may break my bones but discouraging words can’t hold or stop
Me from my destiny, chosen to rock
I wait in the wing for my moment to pop
They say, what about the diploma you got?
I go through the roadblocks lonesome alot
Don’t give a middle finger what you say
You can duck sick unless bucks you pay
I’m a shut you naysayers up someday
And today feels like my lucky day
Don’t understand? Then it must be vague
I’m a spell it out clear cause it must be Shake
I-I-I-I-I’m the leader of the new cool
You might also likeChorus:
Bridge: 2x
I’m invincible, but no superman
But I feel like kryptonite in Lex Luther’s hands
I’m invincible, but not bullet proof
So when the obstacles arise I’m a pull it through
ChorusEmbed
